  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Archdiocese of Lilongwe Integrated HIV and AIDS Response Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Archdiocese of Lilongwe is highly populated and has challenges of people living in abject poverty, unemployed, living with HIV and a young population of mothers. The Archdiocese of Lilongwe through its HIV and AIDS response aims at contributing to the reduction of new HIV infections and quality management of those living with the HIV virus.

By systematically targeting the youth, young couple in rural and peri urban Lilongwe , The Diocese HBC integrated programme will conduct awareness programmes using various strategies and use of appropriate media to convey messages on the causes, effect and impact of HIV in the family and community .

The programme will also try to address stigma, discrimination and denial in communities and to challenge those cultural practices that are causing the further spread of HIV. OVCs will be treated as a special component of the programme as it entails their access to treatment, care and support and education.
The programme will explore opportunities for sustainable livelihoods and other economic empowerment initiatives. By 2015 the programme would have reached about 6000 beneficiaries directly.

The program shall provide adequate and good quality management services to people living with HIV and AIDS through the provision of community palliative and home based care.</narrative>
  </description>
